Defendant Lee Edward Bennett in court with attorney Daniel Gordon Mitchell.  Defendant Lee Edward Bennett in custody.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties advised the court that they have reached a resolution in this matter and that they will not proceed to jury trial.  Jury panel recalled.  Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms. Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.   The Court imposed the following sentence:   
The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 3 years consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 1-1/2 years with credit for  days time served.  Defendant shall serve 1-1/2 years  years   on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but not for  the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 * Provide a DNA sample unless previously taken and on file.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay restitution to Eddie L., in the stipulated amount of $1,900.00, joint and several with co-defendant in 15CF760; restitution to Bouchard's to be determined at a later date, joint and several with co-actor(s) to be named; and pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements from monies taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of defendant's prison funds.  Balances to be paid while on extended supervision.
 * Must have no contact with and be kept separate from co-defendant Phillip Lee.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No contact with Eddie L.;
 - No contact with  Bouchards at 7600 West Capitol Drive, Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Court ordered defendant to pay any balances remaining of the restitution, costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

The parties were advised that as of August 1, 2015, this calendar will be transferred to the Hon. Stephanie G. Rothstein, Branch 25, in Room G55 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Case is continued for restitution hearing before Branch 25 on 8/25/15 at 10:00 a.m.  Videotechnician e-mailed to check availability. Restitution documents remain in the court file.

